WEBVTT

00:10.923 --> 00:12.838
This woman is my sister.

00:12.882 --> 00:14.840
You followed me all the way
to goddamn Europe?

00:14.884 --> 00:16.755
I am here on business, Patricia.

00:16.799 --> 00:18.801
But you don't
know who I am?Jason Jason Ripper.

00:18.844 --> 00:20.803
Would you fuck your mum
to save her life?

00:20.846 --> 00:23.327
MARTHA: He didn't want
to leave Esme alone.

00:26.330 --> 00:28.245
But I persuaded him.

00:28.289 --> 00:29.594
This is on me.

00:29.638 --> 00:30.639
This is my fault.

00:30.682 --> 00:31.988
RIPPER:
Esme was killed

00:32.032 --> 00:33.642
to make you suffer.

00:33.685 --> 00:34.904
Her killer is

00:34.947 --> 00:37.428
watching you squirm.You know who killed her?

00:37.472 --> 00:40.127
You'll give me the name if
I do something for you first.

00:40.170 --> 00:42.303
SYKES:
I used to work for you.

00:42.346 --> 00:44.087
You're Lord Harwood.

00:44.131 --> 00:47.395
Lord James Harwood.

00:47.438 --> 00:49.092
I'm not Harwood!Oh! All right.

00:49.136 --> 00:51.616
JULIAN: The struggle continues,
but it's not going well.

00:51.660 --> 00:53.792
We're losing the battle
on the streets.

00:53.836 --> 00:55.664
We want a truce,
and I asked them to arrange

00:55.707 --> 00:58.623
a meeting between myself and
Frances Gaunt to discuss terms.

00:58.667 --> 00:59.668
Then we'll kill her.

00:59.711 --> 01:01.844
I got the distinct
sense they know.

01:01.887 --> 01:03.454
They know I'm CIA.

01:03.498 --> 01:04.716
I have a job for you,

01:04.760 --> 01:06.022
if you're interested.

01:06.066 --> 01:07.763
You have to succeed tonight

01:07.806 --> 01:09.069
if you want
that name.

01:15.510 --> 01:17.599
Good night, ladies.

01:21.429 --> 01:22.430
Come here.

01:22.473 --> 01:24.649
Should I wake me dad?No.

01:27.957 --> 01:29.045
PRIME MINISTER:
This will sink

01:29.089 --> 01:30.394
the bloody No-Name League
for good.

01:30.438 --> 01:32.092
The widow Mrs. Thwaite
has been appointed

01:32.135 --> 01:33.963
pro tem leader,
pending elections.

01:34.006 --> 01:36.183
England will soon
be yours, my girl.

01:49.370 --> 01:52.547
NEWS READER: Civil disturbances
and street violence

01:52.590 --> 01:55.637
between left- and right-wing
extremist groups

01:55.680 --> 01:59.293
have erupted across the nation
following the unexplained death

01:59.336 --> 02:01.251
of Julian Thwaite,

02:01.295 --> 02:04.646
leader of the so-called
No-Name League.

02:04.689 --> 02:07.431
The prime minister has issued
a statement.

02:07.475 --> 02:10.739
We are facing the grave danger

02:10.782 --> 02:12.175
of outright anarchy...

02:12.219 --> 02:14.438
T-Turn it off.
Turn it off!

02:14.482 --> 02:15.831
Turn it off, Lulu.

02:15.874 --> 02:17.702
Yes, mistress.

02:17.746 --> 02:19.791
Law and order are the walls...

02:19.835 --> 02:21.053
Are you all right, Ginger?

02:21.097 --> 02:22.838
...upon which the root
of democracy sits.

02:22.881 --> 02:24.274
I know that man.

02:24.318 --> 02:26.146
PEGGY: Yeah, that was
the prime minister.

02:26.189 --> 02:28.191
That's the man that hurt me.

02:28.235 --> 02:29.758
BET: That's right.
It is.

02:29.801 --> 02:31.194
You're remembering.

02:31.238 --> 02:32.848
He's remembering.

02:32.891 --> 02:37.157
Well done.
Keep thinking.

02:37.200 --> 02:39.594
Do you remember your name?

02:39.637 --> 02:42.379
J-James.

02:42.423 --> 02:44.294
Bingo!

02:44.338 --> 02:45.904
That's right, love.
You're James.

02:45.948 --> 02:49.125
James what?

02:49.169 --> 02:51.867
James...

02:51.910 --> 02:54.565
H-H-Harwood.

02:54.609 --> 02:57.220
James Harwood.

03:00.223 --> 03:04.053
My name is James Harwood.

03:05.359 --> 03:08.188
Lord James Harwood.

03:08.231 --> 03:09.711
Hooray!

03:09.754 --> 03:12.583
The leader of the Raven Society.

03:12.627 --> 03:17.240
That man... tortured me.

03:17.284 --> 03:19.677
He destroyed my life.

03:21.462 --> 03:22.680
H-He has to die.

03:24.987 --> 03:28.686
He has to die.

04:21.304 --> 04:23.132
Bloody idiots.

04:23.175 --> 04:24.829
You mark my words,
this carries on,

04:24.873 --> 04:26.918
we'll be swimming
in rivers of blood.

04:26.962 --> 04:29.443
We'll be paddling
fucking canoes in it.

04:29.486 --> 04:32.054
Assassinations, riots.

04:32.097 --> 04:33.795
You'd think we was French.

04:39.191 --> 04:41.846
You all right, Daveboy?
Been in the wars again?

04:41.890 --> 04:44.196
It's-- It's just a scratch, pal.

04:44.240 --> 04:46.242
Oh.

04:49.724 --> 04:52.335
Yes, sir,
what can I get you?

04:52.379 --> 04:55.077
I'm good, thank you.

05:00.604 --> 05:03.694
I've been looking for you
for two days.

05:03.738 --> 05:05.696
I was poorly.

05:05.740 --> 05:07.350
What happened?

05:07.394 --> 05:10.658
Well... what can I say?

05:10.701 --> 05:13.182
I cocked up, eh?

05:13.225 --> 05:16.011
One of those things.
Sorry.

05:16.054 --> 05:17.882
I'm sorry,
"one of those things"?

05:17.926 --> 05:19.449
The wrong damn target was hit.

05:19.493 --> 05:21.233
Fair play.

05:21.277 --> 05:24.541
But that wasn't me.
That was the other fella.

05:24.585 --> 05:29.024
Ah, yes, the other fella.

05:30.765 --> 05:32.767
The one who helped you escape.
It was...

05:32.810 --> 05:36.640
It was very kind of him.

05:36.684 --> 05:39.513
Who was that?

05:39.556 --> 05:42.559
Couldn't tell you.
He was wearing a mask.

05:42.603 --> 05:47.390
Ah, a mystery man, eh?

05:47.434 --> 05:50.045
Who was he working for?

05:50.088 --> 05:53.265
And how the hell
would I know that?

05:55.442 --> 05:59.924
Hmm. I'll have to explain
this mess to my bosses.

05:59.968 --> 06:02.274
They'll need answers.

06:02.318 --> 06:03.972
Any input?

06:04.015 --> 06:05.713
No.

06:05.756 --> 06:06.714
Here's my theory.

06:06.757 --> 06:09.238
You were the assassin,

06:09.281 --> 06:10.761
but it wasn't Gaunt
or the Raven Society

06:10.805 --> 06:12.328
who asked you to kill Thwaite.

06:12.372 --> 06:15.418
Nor was it the government.
They have plenty of killers.

06:15.462 --> 06:16.506
Why come to you?

06:18.116 --> 06:21.032
Then a name sprang to mind.

06:21.076 --> 06:23.600
I hear you've become close
friends with John Ripper.

06:23.644 --> 06:26.342
You've been spying on me.

06:26.386 --> 06:29.954
That's not a denial.
I'll take it as a yes.

06:29.998 --> 06:32.392
It was you who killed Thwaite,
and Ripper who sent you.

06:32.435 --> 06:34.785
Take it how you like.
Leave me alone.

06:37.788 --> 06:42.445
Now, why on Earth...
would Ripper want to kill

06:42.489 --> 06:45.187
the leader
of the No-Name League?

06:45.230 --> 06:47.189
What's in it for him?

06:47.232 --> 06:49.017
It's puzzling.

06:49.060 --> 06:52.673
I suspect he's working
for somebody else.

06:52.716 --> 06:57.329
Don't suppose he told you,
did he, who he's working for?

06:57.373 --> 07:00.681
You ask a lot of
questions, Mr. Wayne.

07:00.724 --> 07:02.204
Are you sure you want
the answers?

07:02.247 --> 07:07.122
Well... that sounded vaguely
like a threat.

07:07.165 --> 07:08.340
I don't make threats.

07:08.384 --> 07:10.430
Why tell people what
you're going to do?

07:10.473 --> 07:12.475
You may have started
a civil war.

07:12.519 --> 07:14.521
Haven't you done
enough harm already?

07:14.564 --> 07:16.958
I don't want you to get hurt.

07:17.001 --> 07:19.177
I can't say the same
for my friends.

07:19.221 --> 07:21.876
Some of them aren't
as gentle as I am.

07:21.919 --> 07:25.183
You're not scaring me, Alfred.

07:25.227 --> 07:27.142
I have friends like that, too.

07:37.326 --> 07:39.154
Cheeky... fuck.

07:41.025 --> 07:42.026
What friends has he got?

07:42.070 --> 07:44.159
He means the CIA.

07:46.204 --> 07:47.510
Get to fuck.

07:47.554 --> 07:49.730
He's only posing as
a No-Name League activist.

07:49.773 --> 07:52.036
He's an American agent. CIA.

07:52.080 --> 07:53.995
Evening, Daveboy.All right.

07:54.038 --> 07:55.605
Alfie.

07:55.649 --> 07:57.433
Same again?

07:57.477 --> 07:58.478
Yeah.

07:58.521 --> 08:00.218
And a bag of crisps.

08:02.394 --> 08:03.483
Bastard.

08:06.311 --> 08:07.878
What-- What's got to her?

08:07.922 --> 08:11.012
What's wrong with
asking for crisps?

08:11.055 --> 08:13.710
What?

08:13.754 --> 08:16.452
Oh.

08:27.071 --> 08:30.901
Want some?
There's plenty.

08:30.945 --> 08:33.469
No, thanks.

08:33.513 --> 08:35.950
I did my part.

08:35.993 --> 08:37.734
You promised me a name.

08:37.778 --> 08:40.868
I did.

08:40.911 --> 08:44.088
If there was an angel
on your shoulder, she'd say,

08:44.132 --> 08:48.179
"Turn away now, Alfie.
Walk away.

08:48.223 --> 08:51.879
Serenity is the best revenge."

08:51.922 --> 08:54.142
She'd be wrong.

08:54.185 --> 08:56.536
So long as you're sure.

08:59.800 --> 09:03.673
Go and see Baroness Ortsey,
at Bethlehem Royal Hospital.

09:03.717 --> 09:06.458
She'll tell you who killed Esme.

09:06.502 --> 09:08.548
Who's Baroness Ortsey?

09:09.940 --> 09:12.160
The baroness is...

09:12.203 --> 09:15.206
more of a "what" than a "who."

09:34.748 --> 09:37.751
I'm here to see Baroness Ortsey.

09:37.794 --> 09:39.317
Fill out an application.

09:39.361 --> 09:41.145
We'll process your request
in due course

09:41.189 --> 09:42.843
and contact you by post.

09:42.886 --> 09:45.454
I haven't got time for that.
I need to see her now.

09:45.497 --> 09:47.064
That won't be possible, sir.

09:49.763 --> 09:51.373
John Ripper sent me.

10:25.494 --> 10:28.845
Good morning, ma'am.

10:31.761 --> 10:33.589
ORTSEY:
Good morning, Matron.

10:33.633 --> 10:37.027
Good morning, young man.

10:37.071 --> 10:38.855
What's your name?

10:38.899 --> 10:40.204
Alfred Pennyworth.

10:40.248 --> 10:41.684
Say it again.

10:41.728 --> 10:43.033
Alfred Pennyworth.

10:43.077 --> 10:47.255
I like your voice,
Alfred Pennyworth.

10:47.298 --> 10:49.605
How can I help you, Alfred?

10:49.649 --> 10:52.434
Why are you in there?
What did you do?

10:52.477 --> 10:56.960
Oh, horrors,
my dear, horrors.

10:57.004 --> 10:58.832
Don't ask again
or I'll tell you.

10:58.875 --> 11:00.311
You'll wish you didn't know.

11:00.355 --> 11:03.140
Why are you here, Alfred?

11:03.184 --> 11:07.275
John Ripper said you can tell me
who killed my fiancée.

11:07.318 --> 11:10.017
But now you're here,
you have doubts.

11:10.060 --> 11:15.152
Well, I was expecting,
you know, an informer.

11:15.196 --> 11:16.937
You're a fortune teller,
aren't you?

11:16.980 --> 11:18.765
Oh, dear me, no.

11:18.808 --> 11:22.856
I'm a witch.
Different.

11:22.899 --> 11:25.685
I don't believe in witches and
ghosts and all that malarkey.

11:25.728 --> 11:28.122
The truth doesn't care
what you believe.

11:28.165 --> 11:29.558
All right, then,

11:29.601 --> 11:31.255
who killed my fiancée?

11:31.299 --> 11:33.214
Tell me, and I'll cross
your palm with silver.

11:33.257 --> 11:36.086
Sarcasm is a very
ugly form of wit.

11:36.130 --> 11:38.306
And I don't know who
killed your fiancée.

11:38.349 --> 11:40.264
So you're wasting my time then.

11:40.308 --> 11:41.788
Actually, you're wasting mine.

11:41.831 --> 11:43.615
Sorry to bother you.

11:43.659 --> 11:45.879
Who is the other woman?

11:52.189 --> 11:54.714
What do you mean by that?ORTSEY: What I say.

11:54.757 --> 11:59.762
I... get a very strong feeling
there's another woman involved

11:59.806 --> 12:01.677
in the murder
of your fiancée.

12:01.721 --> 12:04.724
Who is she?

12:04.767 --> 12:06.464
There is no other woman.

12:06.508 --> 12:08.292
Then I'm mistaken.

12:08.336 --> 12:10.686
Never mind.

12:13.776 --> 12:17.867
You're very good...
at standing still and silent.

12:17.911 --> 12:19.608
That's a wonderful gift.

12:19.651 --> 12:21.523
Go on.

12:21.566 --> 12:23.394
Go on?

12:23.438 --> 12:24.787
Do your hocus-pocus.

12:26.963 --> 12:28.399
No, I won't.

12:28.443 --> 12:29.879
Why not?

12:29.923 --> 12:32.795
You're rude and cynical,
and I don't want to help you.

12:32.839 --> 12:34.797
I apologize.Not good enough.

12:34.841 --> 12:36.494
Well, what do you
want me to say?

12:36.538 --> 12:40.803
Say, "Please, Madame, help me.
I'll do anything."

12:44.372 --> 12:46.635
Please, Madame, help me.
I'll do anything.

12:46.678 --> 12:48.898
Very well. I'll help you,

12:48.942 --> 12:51.640
but first,
you must prove your faith in me.

12:51.683 --> 12:53.729
How?

12:53.773 --> 12:56.036
When the moon is full,

12:56.079 --> 12:58.168
bring me a red rose

12:58.212 --> 13:01.128
and the left hand
of a murderer.

13:01.171 --> 13:03.783
And I'll tell you
all you need to know.

13:04.827 --> 13:06.786
Give over.

13:06.829 --> 13:08.875
How about some toad's eyeballs?

13:08.918 --> 13:12.095
You're a nutcase, you
are, or a bloody liar.

13:12.139 --> 13:13.793
Either way, I'm a mug.

13:15.664 --> 13:17.666
You'll be back, Alfred.

13:18.885 --> 13:21.104
You'll be back.

13:30.722 --> 13:32.768
Good to see you, Thomas.

13:32.812 --> 13:35.249
Good to see you, sir.

13:35.292 --> 13:37.817
The folks back home are eager
to hear what went wrong

13:37.860 --> 13:39.862
with the Gaunt operation
from your perspective.

13:39.906 --> 13:42.386
Why it wasn't
Gaunt assassinated?

13:42.430 --> 13:45.215
Well, my man cocked it up.

13:45.259 --> 13:47.565
One of those things.

13:47.609 --> 13:51.569
I was... very upset at first,

13:51.613 --> 13:53.876
but then I analyzed
the situation, and I find...

13:53.920 --> 13:56.879
I can't blame myself.

13:56.923 --> 13:59.316
Not entirely.

13:59.360 --> 14:02.189
In fact,
I rather blame the Company.

14:02.232 --> 14:05.192
I should have been informed
about all of your plans.

14:05.235 --> 14:07.847
Should you indeed? Explain.

14:07.890 --> 14:12.242
I asked myself, who ordered
the death of Julian Thwaite?

14:12.286 --> 14:14.854
Not Gaunt and the Raven Society.

14:14.897 --> 14:16.507
Not Downing Street
or the queen.

14:16.551 --> 14:17.900
No?

14:17.944 --> 14:20.250
The Thwaites were a team.

14:20.294 --> 14:22.949
Why kill one of them
when you should kill both?

14:22.992 --> 14:25.777
Who benefits
from such an odd arrangement?

14:25.821 --> 14:28.868
Only one person--
Undine Thwaite.

14:28.911 --> 14:31.087
She becomes undisputed leader
of the League.

14:31.131 --> 14:32.872
Thin reasoning.

14:32.915 --> 14:34.438
Oh, I have other evidence.

14:34.482 --> 14:36.701
I'm just giving you
the bones here.

14:36.745 --> 14:39.530
If she did kill her husband,
she's one of two things.

14:39.574 --> 14:41.228
A reckless fool,

14:41.271 --> 14:43.970
or a woman with powerful friends
backing her play.

14:44.013 --> 14:45.667
From which I conclude

14:45.710 --> 14:47.364
Undine Thwaite
and the U.S. government

14:47.408 --> 14:49.932
conspired together
to kill Julian Thwaite.

14:49.976 --> 14:51.978
Interesting idea.

14:52.021 --> 14:53.283
That's not a denial.

14:54.328 --> 14:56.547
I can tell you...

14:56.591 --> 14:59.202
that we have an asset very close
to Undine Thwaite.

14:59.246 --> 15:00.638
We control her.

15:00.682 --> 15:01.901
Your asset's John Ripper.

15:01.944 --> 15:04.425
I can't confirm ordeny that.

15:04.468 --> 15:07.689
Now you get to
clean up the mess.

15:07.732 --> 15:09.691
The U.S. congressional elections
are coming up.

15:09.734 --> 15:11.214
America needs
at least six months

15:11.258 --> 15:12.955
of peace and quiet in Europe.

15:12.999 --> 15:15.915
So we need a truce between
the Ravens and the No-Names.

15:18.482 --> 15:20.702
That's an executive
operational memo.

15:20.745 --> 15:22.530
In the next few days,

15:22.573 --> 15:24.880
Undine Thwaite will arrange
another meeting with Gaunt.

15:24.924 --> 15:27.056
Our asset will make
sure you'll be there

15:27.100 --> 15:28.971
as one of Thwaite's team.

15:29.015 --> 15:32.018
This time, she'll offer Gaunt
a sincere and reasonable truce.

15:32.061 --> 15:34.716
If Gaunt accepts, well and good.

15:34.759 --> 15:36.631
If she refuses, she has to go.

15:36.674 --> 15:38.459
Last time we spoke,
Gaunt was dead at any price.

15:38.502 --> 15:39.895
She's scared now.

15:39.939 --> 15:41.244
Nearly dying will do that.

15:41.288 --> 15:42.680
She'll be more flexible.

15:42.724 --> 15:44.552
If Gaunt plays ball, she lives.

15:44.595 --> 15:46.815
If not, you take her out.

15:48.599 --> 15:50.688
Me?

15:50.732 --> 15:52.690
Personally?

15:52.734 --> 15:54.692
Are you ready?

15:56.390 --> 15:58.261
Yes.

15:58.305 --> 16:00.655
I am.

16:05.747 --> 16:07.705
You tricked me!

16:07.749 --> 16:09.707
How's that?

16:09.751 --> 16:11.448
The old lady's a nutter.

16:11.492 --> 16:12.928
Thinks she's a
bloody witch.

16:12.972 --> 16:14.277
And you don't believe her?

16:14.321 --> 16:15.713
'Course I bloody don't.

16:15.757 --> 16:17.193
There's no such
thing as witches.

16:17.237 --> 16:18.978
Sincerely, Alfie.

16:19.021 --> 16:23.765
I know the baroness can help you if
you give her a chance.

16:23.808 --> 16:25.375
If you have a little faith.

16:25.419 --> 16:27.943
You tricked me,
Mr. Ripper.

16:27.987 --> 16:30.641
Suppose I did.

16:30.685 --> 16:32.904
What then?

16:35.907 --> 16:38.823
Well, then, I'm very
disappointed in you.

16:41.870 --> 16:43.872
That's life.

16:43.915 --> 16:45.917
I'm an undertaker.

16:45.961 --> 16:48.398
Nobody I meet is happy.

16:55.144 --> 16:58.017
It's so good to see you
out and about again, Alfie.

16:58.060 --> 16:59.409
Isn't it, Mr. P?

16:59.453 --> 17:01.107
Yes, it is.

17:01.150 --> 17:03.500
Only...

17:03.544 --> 17:06.068
you seem so angry.

17:06.112 --> 17:08.070
Are you angry?

17:08.114 --> 17:10.116
Me? Angry? No.

17:10.159 --> 17:11.900
I'm your mother, Alfie.

17:11.943 --> 17:13.945
I know your moods.

17:15.251 --> 17:18.037
You've every...
every right to be upset

17:18.080 --> 17:20.343
after what you've been through,
son.

17:20.387 --> 17:23.477
So long as you don't...
go back to lolling in bed.

17:23.520 --> 17:25.174
What are you trying to say?

17:25.218 --> 17:27.350
We're worried, Alfie.

17:27.394 --> 17:30.136
All this running about
with John Ripper.

17:30.179 --> 17:31.963
I don't like
to speak ill of anyone,

17:32.007 --> 17:33.530
but he is not a good man.

17:33.574 --> 17:36.577
I'm sorry, but he's not. He's...

17:36.620 --> 17:39.275
Well, I wouldn't like
to say what he is.

17:39.319 --> 17:41.060
He's a bad influence.

17:41.103 --> 17:42.974
Oh, don't worry, Mum.

17:43.018 --> 17:46.152
I know what he is, and he's
got no influence over me.

17:46.195 --> 17:48.502
I'm done with him,
and all that dark shit.

17:48.545 --> 17:50.460
Got to look on
