40:47.140 --> 40:49.316
That's all?That's all.

40:49.359 --> 40:52.232
Sounds like a
damn poor witch.

40:52.275 --> 40:53.712
There must be more.

40:53.755 --> 40:55.235
Same again, lads?

40:56.454 --> 40:58.238
Just a glass of water
for me, please.

40:58.281 --> 41:00.632
For fuck sake,
Spanish, go away.

41:00.675 --> 41:02.808
Shh.

41:02.851 --> 41:06.812
♪ 'Twas there that you
whispered tenderly ♪

41:06.855 --> 41:09.249
♪ That you loved me

41:09.292 --> 41:12.295
♪ You'd always be

41:12.339 --> 41:17.083
♪ My Lili of the lamplight

41:17.126 --> 41:21.043
♪ My own Lili Marlene.

41:41.890 --> 41:43.892
Alfred?

41:46.025 --> 41:47.983
Yeah. What?

41:48.027 --> 41:50.551
You fell asleep for a moment.

41:52.510 --> 41:54.903
I was dreaming.

41:54.947 --> 41:56.688
The tea.
There was something in the tea.

41:56.731 --> 41:59.865
Of course there was
something in the tea.

41:59.908 --> 42:01.910
I'm a witch.

42:04.478 --> 42:07.046
My God.

42:07.089 --> 42:09.048
It was him.

42:09.091 --> 42:10.919
The captain.

42:10.963 --> 42:12.573
He killed Esme.
Is that it?

42:12.617 --> 42:15.533
I don't know. Is it?

42:17.535 --> 42:19.885
The captain.

42:19.928 --> 42:22.888
I hope I've been
of some help.

42:22.931 --> 42:25.586
You have to go now.

42:54.136 --> 42:57.226
Alfie, thank goodness.
Where have you been?

42:57.270 --> 42:59.707
I was out with the boys.

42:59.751 --> 43:01.579
All night?

43:03.711 --> 43:07.106
: Oh, as long
as you're home safe.

43:08.803 --> 43:10.631
Ooh, you're as
cold as ice.

43:11.763 --> 43:13.503
And you've cut yourself.

43:13.547 --> 43:15.810
How'd you do that?

43:15.854 --> 43:18.073
I don't know.

43:18.117 --> 43:20.206
It's nothing.

43:20.249 --> 43:22.425
Oh.

43:47.712 --> 43:50.976
Those posh bastards in London
will swallow their teeth

43:51.019 --> 43:53.456
when they see you,
won't they, Mrs. Spicer?

43:53.500 --> 43:55.371
They'll be extremely surprised.

43:55.415 --> 43:57.330
I am looking rather spiffy,
aren't I?

43:58.897 --> 44:00.899
I'm that proud of you.

44:02.465 --> 44:05.599
I wish you'd wait a bit,
though, before going south.

44:05.643 --> 44:07.514
Get all your strength back.

44:07.557 --> 44:09.690
I am fit as a
fiddle, my dear.

44:09.734 --> 44:12.345
Ooh, ooh!

44:12.388 --> 44:14.652
Wreaking revenge
and redeeming your rights

44:14.695 --> 44:17.655
and saving the country is all
well and good to talk about,

44:17.698 --> 44:21.180
but doing it, well,
it's a different thing.

44:21.223 --> 44:23.138
You'll overtax yourself.

44:23.182 --> 44:25.837
No. I've never
felt more alive.

44:25.880 --> 44:28.753
More full of
passionate energy.

44:28.796 --> 44:32.408
The winds of destiny
are broad abeam.

44:34.802 --> 44:36.499
Thank you, Bet.

44:37.544 --> 44:39.633
Give over.
No.

44:39.677 --> 44:42.462
If it wasn't for your
friendship and generosity,

44:42.505 --> 44:43.811
then I...

44:43.855 --> 44:45.117
PEGGY:
Hello?

44:45.160 --> 44:47.772
I was... I was just
saying, Peggy,

44:47.815 --> 44:52.037
I owe my life and my soul
to your-your deep kindness.

44:52.080 --> 44:54.430
I shall never forget.

44:54.474 --> 44:56.911
Go on.BET: He says he's off

44:56.955 --> 44:59.609
back to London
soon as he's made arrangements.

44:59.653 --> 45:02.047
Oh.

45:02.090 --> 45:03.831
Are you sure you're ready?

45:03.875 --> 45:05.659
See?

45:05.703 --> 45:09.315
I've been very happy here, but
my duty says that I must go.

45:09.358 --> 45:11.621
There's no time to waste.

45:11.665 --> 45:12.753
PEGGY:
Then you must go.

45:12.797 --> 45:15.277
Won't say we won't miss you.

45:15.321 --> 45:18.498
Will you come with me to London?

45:18.541 --> 45:20.065
Both of you?

45:21.762 --> 45:23.329
Really?

45:23.372 --> 45:26.375
Well, I have a battle ahead.

45:26.419 --> 45:28.769
I'll need loyal friends.

45:28.813 --> 45:31.816
Friends that I love and trust.

45:31.859 --> 45:33.774
PEGGY:
London.

45:33.818 --> 45:35.776
I don't know.

45:38.997 --> 45:40.433
We'll go.

45:41.477 --> 45:43.349
Splendid.

45:43.392 --> 45:45.830
And then everybody
laughed at him.

45:45.873 --> 45:47.570
Do you remember?

45:47.614 --> 45:49.137
I do.Aye.

45:49.181 --> 45:51.792
The captain.

45:51.836 --> 45:53.838
Tall, skinny fella. Posh.

45:53.881 --> 45:55.013
Yeah, that's right. Him.

45:55.056 --> 45:56.144
I say!

45:56.188 --> 45:57.319
Steady on, Doris.

46:00.801 --> 46:02.107
What about him?

46:02.150 --> 46:03.586
When we buried Spanish,

46:03.630 --> 46:05.240
he was there, watching.

46:05.284 --> 46:08.113
You were whistling
"Lili Marlene."

46:08.156 --> 46:09.592
I caught his eye.
He looked away.

46:09.636 --> 46:11.725
But for a split second,
I saw his face.

46:15.294 --> 46:17.513
Pure murder.

46:17.557 --> 46:18.688
I forgot all about him.

46:18.732 --> 46:19.864
Never thought of him
all these years.

46:19.907 --> 46:21.387
Alfred...I think it was him.

46:21.430 --> 46:23.781
The captain, he killed
Esme to punish me.

46:23.824 --> 46:25.478
Lots of captains
wanted to punish you.

46:25.521 --> 46:26.784
No, I think it was him.

46:26.827 --> 46:28.611
The witch told you this?

46:28.655 --> 46:30.483
Well, not exactly. No.

46:30.526 --> 46:33.791
I saw him-- in a dream.

46:33.834 --> 46:37.707
Well, more of a
vision, really.

46:37.751 --> 46:39.666
He was crystal clear, though.

46:39.709 --> 46:41.407
He has been waiting.

46:41.450 --> 46:43.496
Waiting all this time
to pay me back.

46:43.539 --> 46:46.629
For embarrassing him
five years ago?

46:46.673 --> 46:48.153
Now, look, if you could see

46:48.196 --> 46:49.937
how he looked at me,
you'd understand.

46:51.765 --> 46:54.855
I remembered his name.

46:54.899 --> 46:58.293
ALFRED:
Captain John
Fitz-Smytth Curzon,

46:58.337 --> 47:01.906
Third Battalion,
Rutland Fusiliers.

47:01.949 --> 47:04.169
I called the Army
Records Office.

47:04.212 --> 47:06.867
He survived the war.

47:06.911 --> 47:08.913
That's where he lives.

47:08.956 --> 47:10.740
Alfie,

47:10.784 --> 47:12.873
just so we're clear,

47:12.917 --> 47:14.919
you've no proof
yet-- nothing.

47:14.962 --> 47:17.573
A feeling.

47:17.617 --> 47:20.272
No bloodshed.

47:20.315 --> 47:22.187
Please say yes.

47:25.190 --> 47:27.583
Yeah.

47:51.042 --> 47:53.044
ALFRED:
What the fuck is this?

48:00.703 --> 48:01.922
"Ha ha.

48:01.966 --> 48:04.359
"A little too
late, my friend.

48:04.403 --> 48:06.535
"Don't think I'm
sorry or scared.

48:06.579 --> 48:09.625
I'm glad you know the truth."

